<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-05-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-05-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="339" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d339">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">701.0090/22: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Harrison</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-05-07">May 7, 1942</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>1160. Department’s 879, April 7, paragraph 10. Department now
                                informed that <hi rend="italic">Gripsholm</hi> cannot leave Sweden
                                before May 25 and will possibly be delayed until May 30. Accordingly
                                vessel will be unable to depart from United States until June 10 to
                                15 arriving at Lourenço Marques 1 month later. Swiss representatives
                                Par East should be informed urgently and requested to communicate
                                this information to Department’s officers.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>